ProtoResult:
. "Let \begin{equation} c_n=f(n),\quad n\ge k, \end{equation} 
   where $f$ is positive, nonincreasing, and locally integrable
   on $[k,\infty)$ Then \begin{equation} \sum c_n<\infty 
   \end{equation} if and only if \begin{equation} \int^\infty_k
   f(x)\,dx<\infty. \end{equation}"
